SEC. 7.

Equipment and Supplies.

â The Department of Health shall. aside from drugs and medicines, provide each infirmary with the following equipment:

Basic sets for abnormal maternal delivery;

Minor surgical sets for suturing and repair of wounds;

Transfusion or infusion sets;

Microscope and laboratory sets for cross matching and typing, and identification of malarial and amoebic parasites;

Opthalmoscopic and otoscopic sets for EENT cases;

Trachetomy sets;

Basic fracture set boards or metal frames for fractures;

Intravenous sets;

Ambo bags for respiratory resuscitation; and

Local anesthetics or narcoleptics.

SEC. 8.

Transfer of Personnel, Assets and Records.

â The properties, records, obligations and appropriations of the municipal main health units concerned shall be transferred to the infirmaries so established.

SEC. 9.

Rules and Regulations.

â The Secretary of Health shall issue the necessary rules and regulations for the effective implementation of this Act.
